In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation declaring June 2020 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. The proclamation highlights the significant contributions of African-American artists in shaping America's music culture. It mentions various genres such as blues, jazz, gospel, rock and roll, rap, and hip-hop, and acknowledges the role of African-American music in expressing both pain and joy. The proclamation also pays tribute to artists like Sam Cooke, Mahalia Jackson, Whitney Houston, Ray Charles, and Little Richard, emphasizing their impact on breaking down racial barriers and inspiring the nation. President Trump calls upon public officials, educators, and the American people to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and appreciation for African-American music.